<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Flash:
[I]Hello!
First, my own little RPG history:
I'm pretty much an RPG newbie. The only RPG I've ever played is Ultima 4, and it was my surfing on Nemisis Dragon's Ultima Homepage that brought me here. I liked what I saw, especially this forum, but as I did not know if I would like Divinity, I did not dare to register, because I don't like popping out of nowhere doing some posts and then disappearing again. But after having played the demo, I know that I like it, so I can now come to what this post does exist for. The suggestions:
-I think there should be an option to turn of the auto-unpause. I don't like that I equip a new weapon, use a potion, etc, and get immediately bashed by all those skeletons. I want to determine when the pause is over.
-There should be an option to auto-pause on menu popup. Very often when I open a vase, look at my stats, or something similar, I get attacked behind the popup window without noticing it.
-In the main statistics the player's strength, agility etc. should be shown clarifying if they are increased by a magical item. An example: I was using a rogue's staff, which increased my agility (I think). When I leveled up I thought that my agility was 21 and didn't increase it, because the weapon I wanted to equip next needed 20. But in fact my agility was only 19 and I could not equip the weapon. I think it would be nice if it had showed 19+2.
-It would be nice if I could click on the equipments in the equipment window, and it would open my inventory, with the right tab already selected, so that I could easily choose a new eqipment.
-Personally I think it would be nice to have an 'extremely easy' difficulty setting, because I'm one of the guys who even get killed in a normal game's tutorial  ;)
-And last but not least I would like to add that I support the No-Fog-of-War-movement  ;)

Thats pretty much everything I have to say for now, if anything has been discussed before, my apologies, I did read a lot in these forums, but not everything. Also my apologies if I did not express myself clearly, especially with my limited english skills.

To Dorien: I wonder which Ultima Fansites you are browsing on. They tell you the wrong release dates and don' tell you about the workarounds for the crappy memory systems. You can find them here:
 [URL=http://exult.sourceforge.net]exult.sourceforge.net[/URL] 
 [URL=http://members.iinet.net.au/~rsd/]http://members.iinet.net.au/~rsd/[/URL] 
You can get every Ultima upgrades here:
 [URL=http://reconstruction.voyd.net]reconstruction.voyd.net[/URL] [/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
